{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620661"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:45:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:45:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16642"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16642"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.55,0.14,0.07,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76526"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9333"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16642"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62023"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5251"},{"type":"tags","id":"10106"},{"type":"tags","id":"10145"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22106"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22639"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76526"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESelective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMs) are an important class of drugs used in the treatment and prevention of breast cancer and osteoporosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action of selective oestrogen receptor modulators?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Selectively targets tissues as an oestrogen agonist","Acts as tissue-specific oestrogen agonist or antagonist","Modulates oestrogen binding at all oestrogen receptors","Degrades oestrogen receptors in all tissues","Selectively blocks oestrogen production in all tissues"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESERMs exhibit a \u003Cstrong\u003Etissue-specific oestrogen agonist or antagonist\u003C/strong\u003E effect depending on the target tissue. This unique property allows them to block oestrogen effects in some tissues while mimicking oestrogen in others.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelectively targets tissues as an oestrogen agonist\u003C/strong\u003E - This is incomplete as SERMs can act as either agonists or antagonists depending on the tissue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EModulates oestrogen binding at all oestrogen receptors\u003C/strong\u003E - SERMs have selective effects in different tissues rather than affecting all receptors uniformly\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDegrades oestrogen receptors in all tissues\u003C/strong\u003E - SERMs bind to and modulate receptor function rather than causing receptor degradation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelectively blocks oestrogen production in all tissues\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the mechanism of aromatase inhibitors, not SERMs which act at the receptor level\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFor example, tamoxifen acts as an oestrogen antagonist in breast tissue (useful for treating breast cancer) but as an agonist in bone (helping prevent osteoporosis) and endometrium (potentially increasing endometrial cancer risk). These tissue-specific effects are due to different coregulator proteins present in different tissues that interact with the SERM-receptor complex.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Selective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMs) have tissue-specific effects, acting as oestrogen agonists in some tissues and antagonists in others.","Tamoxifen acts as an oestrogen antagonist in breast tissue but an agonist in bone and endometrium.","The tissue-specific effects of SERMs depend on the presence of different oestrogen receptor coregulators in different tissues."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62023"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16642"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62023"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T16:50:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T16:50:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9333"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76526"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student